        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 4:53PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 451 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Monsey, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
New City, Ossining, Monsey, Nanuet, Haverstraw, Upper Nyack, Spring
Valley, West Haverstraw, Valley Cottage, Airmont, Congers,
Croton-on-Hudson, Chestnut Ridge, Briarcliff Manor, and Hillcrest.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
